label: stateCode
comment: The state code corresponding to this observation.

comment: Name of the state corresponding to this observation.

label: districtCode
comment: The district code corresponding to this observation.

label: districtName

label: subdistrictCode
comment: The subdistrict code corresponding to this observation.

label: subdistrictName
comment: Name of the subdistrict corresponding to this observation.  A subdistrict is also called as a tehsil, mandal, tahsil, tahasil, taluka, taluk, or taluq across the Indian states.

label: clusterCode
comment: The cluster code corresponding to this observation.

label: clusterName
comment: Name of the cluster corresponding to this observation. A cluster or a firkas represents a group of villages.

label: villageCode
comment: The village code corresponding to this observation.

label: villageName
comment: Name of the village corresponding to this observation.

label: revenueDivision
comment: Name of the revenue division in a district corresponding to this observation.

label: revenueDivisionCode
comment: The revenue division code corresponding to this observation

label: wardID
comment: Ward ID corresponding to this observation.

label: wardName
comment: Ward name corresponding to this observation.

label: zoneID
comment: Zone ID corresponding to this observation.

label: zoneName
comment: Zone name corresponding to this observation.

label: countryName
comment: Name of the country corresponding to this observation.

label: countryCode
comment: Name of the country code corresponding to this observation.
